  <Properties>
    <publishDate>
      <Value>2026-04-15T09:00:00</Value>
    </publishDate>
    <summary>
      <Value><![CDATA[Construction of the new Greenfield Recycling Centre on Mill Lane has been completed three months ahead of schedule.]]></Value>
    </summary>
    <main>
      <Value><![CDATA[<p class="govuk-body">The new £2.4 million recycling centre opens to the public from Monday 20 April. The site replaces the older facility on Station Road, which closes the previous Friday.</p><p class="govuk-body">The new centre accepts a wider range of materials including small electricals, batteries, and household chemicals. It is open seven days a week, 8am to 6pm.</p><p class="govuk-body">Cabinet member for the environment, Councillor Sarah Jenkins, said: "This is a real step forward for recycling in our district. We're confident residents will find the new layout easier and quicker to use."</p>]]></Value>
    </main>
  </Properties>
</Content>
